        "summary": {
          "diffs": [
            {
              "file": "bench-artifacts/code-review-diagnosis.md",
              "patch": "Index: bench-artifacts/code-review-diagnosis.md\n===================================================================\n--- bench-artifacts/code-review-diagnosis.md\t\n+++ bench-artifacts/code-review-diagnosis.md\t\n@@ -0,0 +1,15 @@\n+# Code Review Diagnosis\n+\n+## Findings\n+\n+- **Missing amount validation**: Both `chargeCustomer` and `refundCustomer` functions accept `amount` parameter without any validation or sanitization, risking invalid transaction amounts or potential for abuse.\n+\n+- **Missing gateway error handling**: Both functions call `gateway.charge()` and `gateway.refund()` without waiting for the Promise to resolve, without catching `Promise.rejection`, and without including error information in the return value.\n+\n+## Residual Risks\n+\n+- **Silent failures**: If gateway operations fail (network issues, insufficient funds, card declined, timeout), the caller receives no error response since the functions return `{ ok: true }` unconditionally.\n+\n+- **No amount constraints**: Unsanitized amounts could include floating point issues, negative values, or excessively large values, causing unexpected behavior.\n+\n+- **No transaction tracking**: No record of failed transactions, no error codes from gateway, no way to retry.\n",
              "additions": 15,
              "deletions": 0,
              "status": "added"
            }
          ]
        },
